":"当Lord Simon de Cooper II于1375年出生在苏格兰費伏时，他的父亲Symon Cooper II35岁，母亲Margery Cotton34岁。他于1407年与Agnes Appleton de Bois在英国英格兰史洛普爾结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1422年在英国史洛普爾享年47岁，埋葬在英国英格兰史洛普爾。"},"hr":{"1375–1422":"1375.–1422.","1385–1455":"1385–1455","1340–1422":"1340–1422.","1341–Female":"1341–preminula","about 1360":"oko 1360.","1422":"1422.","1455":"1455","1375":"1375.","1341":"1341","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1407":"1407.","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Škotska, United Kingdom","Bedford, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedford, Bedfordshire, England"},"cs":{"1375–1422":"1375–1422","1385–1455":"1385–1455","1340–1422":"1340–1422","1341–Female":"1341–Zesnulá","about 1360":"okolo 1360","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1341":"1341","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1407":"1407","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Skotsko, United Kingdom","Bedford, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedford, Bedfordshire, Anglie"},"da":{"1375–1422":"1375–1422","1385–1455":"1385–1455","1340–1422":"1340–1422","1341–Female":"1341–Afdød","about 1360":"omkring 1360","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1341":"1341","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1407":"1407","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Skotland, United Kingdom","Bedford, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedford, Bedfordshire, England"},"nl":{"1375–1422":"1375–1422","1385–1455":"1385–1455","1340–1422":"1340–1422","1341–Female":"1341–Overleden","about 1360":"circa 1360","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1341":"1341","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1407":"1407","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bedford, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedford, Bedfordshire, England"},"en":{"1375–1422":"1375–1422","1385–1455":"1385–1455","1340–1422":"1340–1422","1341–Female":"1341–Deceased","about 1360":"about 1360","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1341":"1341","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1407":"1407","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom","Bedford, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedford, Bedfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Cooper","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: occupational name for a maker and repairer of wooden vessels such as barrels, tubs, buckets, casks, and vats, from Middle English <i>couper</i>, <i>cowper</i> (apparently from Middle Dutch <i>kūper</i>, a derivative of <i>kūp</i> ‘tub, container’, which was borrowed independently into English as <i>coop</i>). The prevalence of the surname, its cognates, and equivalents bears witness to the fact that this was one of the chief specialist trades in the Middle Ages throughout Europe. In North America, the English surname has absorbed some cases of like-sounding cognates from other languages, for example Dutch   Kuiper  .","Americanized form of Jewish (Ashkenazic) <b>Kupfer</b> and <b>Kupper</b> (see   Kuper  ).","Dutch: occupational name for a buyer or merchant, Middle Dutch <i>coper</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Kuiper","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Dutch Gerrit, Hendrik, Willem, Harm, Klaas, Kort, Marinus, Nicolaas, Wouter.","Dutch: occupational name for a cooper, Middle Dutch <i>cup(e)re</i>."]},{"name":"Couper","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Cooper  ."]},{"name":"Hooper","meanings":["English (southwestern): occupational name for a cooper, someone who fitted wooden or metal hoops on wooden casks and barrels, or a barrel-maker, from Middle English <i>hoper</i>, an agent derivative of <i>hop</i> ‘hoop, band’. Compare   Cooper  ."]},{"name":"Coop","meanings":["English (Lancashire): metonymic occupational name for a cooper, from Middle English <i>coupe</i>, <i>cupe</i> ‘tub, cask’ (from Latin <i>cūpa</i>), probably used for a cooper; compare   Cooper  . In some cases the surname may have been derived from a pub or house sign.","Americanized form of German or Dutch   Koop  .","History: It was David Koop (his father's surname also spelled <i>Kupe</i>) from Germany whose surname was changed to <i>Coop</i> after he settled in PA toward the end of the 18th century. He later moved to VA."]}]},{"name":"Simon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."],"variants":[{"name":"Simen","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":7,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Lord Simon de Cooper II was born in 1375, in Fife, Scotland, his father, Symon Cooper II, was 35 and his mother, Margery Cotton, was 34. He married Agnes Appleton de Bois in 1407, in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1422, in Shropshire, England, at the age of 47, and was buried in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1375–1422":"1375–1422","1385–1455":"1385–1455","1340–1422":"1340–1422","1341–Female":"1341–Surnud","about 1360":"umbes 1360","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1341":"1341","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1407":"1407","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Bedford, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedford, Bedfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1375–1422":"1375–1422","1385–1455":"1385–1455","1340–1422":"1340–1422","1341–Female":"1341–Kuollut","about 1360":"noin 1360","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1341":"1341","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1407":"1407","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bedford, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedford, Bedfordshire, England"},"fr":{"1375–1422":"1375–1422","1385–1455":"1385–1455","1340–1422":"1340–1422","1341–Female":"1341–Décédée","about 1360":"environ 1360","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1341":"1341","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1407":"1407","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Bedford, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedford, Bedfordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Lord Simon de Cooper II est né en 1375, à Fife, Écosse, son père, Symon Cooper II, avait 35 ans et sa mère, Margery Cotton, avait 34 ans. Il a épousé Agnes Appleton de Bois en 1407, à Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1422, à Shropshire, Angleterre, à l’âge de 47 ans, et a été enterré à Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1375–1422":"1375–1422","1385–1455":"1385–1455","1340–1422":"1340–1422","1341–Female":"1341–Verstorben","about 1360":"um 1360","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1341":"1341","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1407":"1407","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Schottland, United Kingdom","Bedford, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedford, Bedfordshire, England","lifeSummary":"Als Lord Simon de Cooper II 1375 in Fife, Scotland geboren wurde, war sein Vater Symon Cooper II 35 und seine Mutter Margery Cotton 34. Er hat 1407 in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom Agnes Appleton de Bois geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb 1422 im Alter von 47 Jahren in Shropshire, England und wurde in Shropshire, England, United Kingdom begraben."},"ht":{"1375–1422":"1375–1422","1385–1455":"1385–1455","1340–1422":"1340–1422","1341–Female":"1341–Desede","about 1360":"about 1360","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1341":"1341","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1407":"1407","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Angletè, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Ecosse, United Kingdom","Bedford, Bedfordshire, England":"Bedford, Bedfordshire, England"},"hu":{"1375–1422":"1375–1422","1385–1455":"1385–1455","1340–1422":"1340–1422","1341–Female":"1341–elhunyt","about 1360":"1360 körül","1422":"1422","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1341":"1341","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1407":"1407","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Anglia, United Kingdom","Fife, S